Lufthansa’s BMI Sale May Be Complicated by Pensions, Times Says

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-10-16T08:30:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/lufthansa-s-bmi-sale-may-be-complicated-by-pensions-times-says.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA) ’s possible
sale of its BMI unit may be complicated by pension liabilities,
the Sunday Times reported, citing a letter from BMI pension
trustees Chairman Clive Grimley.  Grimley has written to Lufthansa and regulators requesting
involvement in any takeover talks, according to the report.
BMI’s pension plan has a deficit of more than 100 million pounds
($158 million), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in  London  
